# Anti-Sleep Vibrator Alarm

## Overview

The Anti-Sleep Vibrator Alarm is a wearable drowsiness detection system designed to improve driver safety by alerting users when signs of fatigue are detected. The system uses an infrared (IR) sensor to monitor eye activity and a buzzer to generate an alarm when prolonged eye closure is detected.

The prototype is mounted on a spectacle frame, making it lightweight, portable, and suitable for real-time use during driving or other attention-critical activities.

---

## Problem Statement

Driver drowsiness is one of the major causes of road accidents, especially during long-distance travel and night driving. Many existing solutions are expensive and require complex hardware.

This project aims to provide a simple, low-cost, and wearable solution for detecting drowsiness and alerting the user before accidents occur.

---

