## Working Principle

The IR sensor continuously emits infrared light and monitors the reflected signal from the eye region.

When the eyes are open, the reflected infrared signal remains within the normal operating range.

When the eyes remain closed for a longer duration, the reflected signal changes significantly.

This change is detected by the sensor circuitry, which activates the buzzer.

The buzzer alerts the user, helping prevent fatigue-related accidents.

